\b0 This folder describes the calculations and measurements made by AKHeitman on December, 2013 while rigA and rigB were still at the Salk (but EJ was already up at Stanford).\
Scalar measurements of power through the standard optical path carefully, in both rigs, using different focusing lens, with and without the cylinder and with and without a board. AKHeitman also made estimates of the size of a pixel on the board through the 6.5x an approximates between 4.2 and 4.8 microns squared per pixel.\
\
All spectrum measurements were done else where  (CRT spectral emissions by GDField in 2007, LMS cone spectral sensitivity from Rieke lab, UDT head sensitivity .. i'm not sure).
