\b Note on cone effective area
\b0 \
- According to an email interchange with Professor Fred Rieke, if we shine light through the ganglion cell layer, the effective area should be .6 microns squared.  If we shine light directly to the photoreceptor side than they use .37 microns squared as their estimate.  \
